verbose_text: The relative expression of V. anguillarum 16S rRNA in the head kidney prior to infection was close to zero on days 2 and 7, whereas on day 19 (4 days post-infection) the expression of 16S rRNA was highest (but not statistically significant) in fish that received the control plasmid (a 200-fold increase compared to pre-challenge values, approximately) and PBS injected controls (a 150-fold increase, approximately) (XREF_FIG B).
